2021 by mail: 20 packages per household - and a leap in their weight
46.6 million packages arrived in Israel during 2021 - similar to 2020
The average weight per pack is 435 grams - a jump of 36% compared to 2020
The busiest month: December, when the average package weight was 524 grams.
In 2021, 46.6 million mail packages arrived in Israel, an average of almost 20 packages per household, according to Israel Post data obtained by Israel Hayom.
The number of packages arriving in 2021 is similar to 2020, when 46.5 million packages arrived in Israel, and lower than 2019, when 61.6 million packages arrived.
However, this year there was a jump of more than 36% a year in the weight of packages that came from abroad.
In 2021, 20,253 tonnes of products from abroad arrived in Israel, up 36 per cent from 14,860 tonnes in 2020, and 16,743 tonnes in 2019.
Changes in consumption habits.
The average weight per package has jumped 60% in two years - from 272 grams in 2019 to 435 grams in 2021.
The increase in the weight of the packages is mainly influenced by two main trends, both from the seller and from the buyer: the major shopping sites abroad combine items for one shipment and no longer send each product from the "shopping basket" in a separate package.
On the part of the Israeli consumer, the rapid delivery of shipments, within a few days of the order, supports the purchase of more everyday products such as clothing and gifts, which the purchasers wish to receive shortly after the purchase.
Even in 2021, as in 2020 and 2019, the month with the highest number of overseas packages and the highest number of items is December, with 4.2 million packages weighing a total of 2,200 tons.
In December, the average weight per pack was 524 grams, 20% higher than the annual average weight.
The Black Friday Effect.
More packages arrived in December than in any other month, likely due to November shopping holidays such as Chinese Singles Day, Black Friday and Cyber Monday.
The big orders start arriving in Israel between a week and two weeks after the purchase.
