Many employees can receive a high amount, since four out of five employees are eligible for tax refunds.
In practice, however, several tens of thousands of employees serve annually.
If you think that these funds will go down the drain anyway, think again: Employees can apply for income tax returns for six years back.
Tax: On conducted an in-depth study of 4,000 of its customers regarding tax returns during 2020.
The company has more than 30,000 customers, so the sample reflects their distribution in terms of population groups and gender, ages and geography.
The data indicate that during 2020, due to the outbreak of the COVID-19 crisis and the expenditure of hundreds of thousands of workers to the IAF, there were a number of significant changes, centered on a 15% increase in the average return to a household of NIS 4,300 per year.
The reason is that the fees are lower than the salaries and therefore a gap is created between what the employee paid as tax and what he actually needs.
By the way, the highest refund received in 2020 by a customer of the company was NIS 121,054 for refunds over the last 6 years.
What can I get a tax refund for?
One of the reasons to get tax refunds is a change in the workplace.
Eighty-one percent of people who changed jobs during the year received a tax refund of an average of NIS 2,943.
