The data show that 74% of women who gave birth and were on maternity leave for more than 16 weeks were entitled to a reimbursement of NIS 3,538 on average for that year.
Another reason for reimbursement is donations.
100% of people who donate and pay taxes have been reimbursed.
Another factor for reimbursement is the failure to register credit points for alimony. 63%
The divorcees did not update a credit point for alimony, and therefore the tax refund for each year that such a credit point was not updated is NIS 2,616.
Unemployment: 93% of those who became ill or were unemployed and earned more than NIS 12,000 received a tax refund of NIS 4021 for that year.
Other reasons for tax refunds are: reimbursement for life insurance payments, life insurance on a mortgage, exculpatory return, reimbursement for losses in securities, non-registration of credit points for a man for birth and distribution of tax refunds by geographic location.
- 94% of people who deposited for personal life insurance or for taking out a mortgage were eligible for a tax refund.
