100% of those who moved to a beneficiary settlement received a tax refund for the transition year, since approval for residency in a beneficiary settlement is given only after 12 months from the date the resident becomes a beneficiary resident, and thus the first year is actually paid full tax.
79% of customers holding securities were entitled to a tax return for the said years.
However, those who hold securities are important to check every year since losses are not rolled over from year to year but only through the submission of a report.
Fifty-six percent of men who have a child do not write a year-of-birth credit on their pay slip.
The return rate can reach tens of thousands of shekels over 6 years.
This is a phenomenon that exists mainly in the Arab sector.
CEO of Tax: on, Tal Carmon: "The COVID-19 crisis has made the salaried public in Israel much more active.
He is interested, checking and demanding what he deserves in returns from the IRS.
It turns out that sitting at home, in the PLO or after the dismissal of hundreds of thousands of Israelis for months on end, has caused many employees to examine in depth what they deserve from the state.
