Exemption from isolation for the vaccinated and recovering from non-red countries, foreign tourists are returning.
Landings in Israel received notices from the Ministry of Health that they are exempt from the isolation requirement upon receiving a negative response to the COVID-19 test
Only later did the ministry issue an official statement that it was only passengers from orange countries, although returnees from red countries also reported receiving the notice.
In addition, tourists from orange destinations will be able to enter the country and many red destinations are expected to be removed from the list.
In the midst of a pandemic - the end to quarantine?
The Ministry of Health sent notices to the returnees Monday morning, stating that they are exempt from quarantine upon receiving a negative response to the COVID-19 test they performed after landing in Israel.
They also come from red states.
Some of the messages sent informed the returnees that they could be released after receiving a negative reply or after 24 hours at the latest, and some of them received the exemption after receiving the negative reply.
It was only after that that the Ministry of Health issued official notices stating that as of midnight, 4.1.2022, vaccinated or recovering, those returning from orange countries will undergo a PCR test at Ben Gurion Airport and will be quarantined for 24 hours or until they receive a negative result (whichever comes first).
The decision will be anchored in the order of the Director General of the Ministry of Health and will be submitted for the approval of the Knesset Health Committee.
The ministry clarified that vaccinated or recovering persons who have already returned to Israel from an orange country and received a negative result from their PCR test at the entrance to Israel, will complete their isolation at midnight and are not obligated to perform a second test.
However, travellers from red countries reported that they had also received the message.
Those who have not been vaccinated or recovered from an orange country will be placed in home isolation for 14 days, with the possibility of shortening isolation with a negative result in a pcr test performed from the 7th day of landing in Israel (the day of landing is the first day).
The decision to lift most of the restrictions on flying, and especially on the vaccinated, comes a day before the High Court of Justice hearing submitted by the Travel Offices Association, the Open Skies Headquarters and the Hotels Association.
In tomorrow's hearing, the petitioners are expected to demand that all other red states be removed from the list, with Professor Itamar Grotto backing them in his opinion.
Strangers can also come in.
The Prime Minister and the Ministers of Foreign Affairs, Health, Interior, Tourism and Transportation agreed that as of Sunday, 9.1.2022, vaccinated/recovering foreigners (according to the Ministry of Health's definition) from orange countries will be allowed to enter - this is subject to filling out an online form in advance, performing a PCR or antigen test before boarding the plane, performing a PCR test at the entrance to Israel and then entering isolation for 24 hours or receiving a negative test (whichever comes first).
Unvaccinated/non-recovering foreigners (according to the definition of the Ministry of Health) will not be allowed to enter Israel.
Foreigners from red states, except those whose entry was approved by the exceptions committee, will not be allowed to enter Israel.
Teams will not be renewed at this time.
What about red states?
The Committee for Classification of Countries in the Ministry of Health recommends that the government remove from the list of red countries and transfer to the list of orange countries: South Africa, Hungary, Nigeria, Spain, Portugal, France, Canada.
The countries currently remaining on the list are the United Arab Emirates, the United States, Ethiopia, the United Kingdom, Tanzania, Mexico, Switzerland and Turkey.
Another option being considered by the Ministry of Health is to exempt vaccinated people returning from red states from isolation.
It is currently unclear whether there is any connection between the messages received this morning by those returning to Israel and the guidelines that may be received by the Ministry of Health on this issue.
The Health Department has not yet responded.
The sky is beginning to open: the Ministry of Health is changing the restrictions on the gates of the country
Vaccinated persons returning from orange countries will be subject to 24-hour isolation.
The United States, Turkey, the United Kingdom and the United Arab Emirates will be red.
After long weeks in which it was very difficult to find a destination to which it was possible to fly without restrictions, and after all those returning from abroad were forced to quarantine, alongside the ban on tourists entering Israel - yesterday it was decided to change the procedures and significantly ease the restrictions on Ben Gurion Airport.
The Ministry of Health decided to recommend abolishing the three-day quarantine requirement for Israelis returning from orange countries.
So far, all vaccinated or recovering according to the definitions of the Ministry of Health who returned from an orange state - have been charged with isolation for three days, subject to two coronavirus tests.
Now, the isolation that the vaccinated and recovering returnees from orange countries will have to undergo is for a maximum of 24 hours, or until the results of the COVID-19 tests that are performed after landing at Ben Gurion Airport (whichever comes first) are received.
A person who is not vaccinated or recovering will nevertheless be required to enter seven days of isolation subject to two coronavirus tests, or 14 days without the second test, even if he returned from an orange country and even if he returned from a red country.
A vaccinated or recovering person returning from a red state must also be in full isolation.
The latest list of red countries recommended by the Ministry of Health, which still needs to be approved by the government, includes the United States, Turkey, Tanzania, Ethiopia, Mexico, the United Kingdom, Switzerland and the United Arab Emirates.
In all countries, with the exception of Turkey, the average number of positive visitors to Israel in the past two weeks is more than 5% of the total number of arrivals, which automatically puts them on the list of red countries.
The rate of increase among patients from Turkey is rapid, the rate of positive return from Turkey is just over 4%, so it was decided to add it to the list of red states.
The most prominent countries to be removed from the red list: France, Spain, Portugal and Canada.
Meanwhile, as of 9 January, tourists vaccinated according to Ministry of Health requirements will be able to enter Israel without the need for isolation, similar to the conditions of Israelis returning from an orange state.
In this case, too, the decision is subject to the government's approval, which will discuss the matter in the coming days.
It is important to note that there are few cases in which the government does not approve the Health Ministry's recommendations in this area.
The tourists against the restrictions.
